Description: Washington DNR Pilot Project
Name of burn unit (i.e., Angel, 25 Mile, Sherman Creek, Chumstick ZUI, Paradise 90, Orion 2)
ID for season of Rx burn (i.e., "Fall2016" or "Spring2017").
Sampling episode short name (i.e., PRE, POST)
Calendar date of wired log installation (DD-MMM-YY)
Plot number (i.e., 1-20) of nearest overstory permanent plot
Pin number (i.e., 1-16).
Status of individual pin following Rx fire (i.e., "OK" (ignited), "NI" (not ignited), "PF" (pin fell), "NP" (no pin)).
Type of pin placed (i.e., "S" (Steel pin), "W" (welding rod)).
Pre Rx fire distance, in mm, from the top of pin to the highest point of the surface material (SM).
ID or type of SM that is dominant at each pin (i.e., "LP" (long needle pine), "SF" (spruce-fir-hemlock)).
Distance, in mm, from the highest point of the surface material (SM) to the boundary of SM and Duff.
Pre Rx fire distance, in mm, from the highest point of the surface material (SM) to the boundary of SM and Duff. Same as SMDepth_mm (ignore).
Difference, in mm, of surface material (SM) consumed during Rx fire (i.e., SM_PostDepth_mm - SM_PreDepth_mm)).
Post Rx fire distance, in mm, from the highest point of the surface material (SM) to the boundary of SM and Duff.
ID or type of Duff that is dominant at each pin (i.e., "LP" (long needle pine), "SF" (spruce-fir-hemlock)).
Post Rx fire distance, in mm, from the top of pin to the highest point of the remaining surface material (SM), or Duff.
Post Rx fire distance, in mm, from the top of pin to the soil/duff boundary.
Derived value of pre Rx fire duff depth, in mm, (i.e., pinToSoil_mm - SMDepth_mm).
Difference, in mm, of Duff consumed during Rx fire (i.e., Duff_PostDepth_mm - Duff_PreDepth_mm).
Derived value of post Rx fire duff depth, in mm, (i.e., pinToSoil_mm - pinToRemaining_mm).
